	<title>Confusing behaviour when editing a Readonly file.</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">I changed the Readonly properties of a file to Yes.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.2">Then I double clicked on the file to bring it up in the editor.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.3">When I tried to enter something in the editor, I got the message:
File 'xxxx' is read-only.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.4">Do you wish to make it writable?</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">I clicked Yes to dismiss the dialog.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.2">Then I was able to input in the editor.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.3">I did a Save on the file, and got error:
Operation failed.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.4">File sytem input or output error.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.5">Details: Message report from file system: File filelist_ro cannot be saved on SLES8RM.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.6">You do not have write access to the file.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">I clicked OK to dismiss the dialog.</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.2">Close the editor (did not see a * which was used to mark the file is dirty in the editor tab).</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.3">Opened it again.</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.4">I could see the contents I just put in was there.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="4">
			<sentence id="4.1">Refreshed this file in System View tree, but the read only property is still set to Yes.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="5">
			<sentence id="5.1">If I tried to edit the file again, I got the dialog 
"File 'xxxx' is read-only.</sentence>
			<sentence id="5.2">Do you wish to make it writable?"</sentence>
			<sentence id="5.3">again.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
